    <item>
      <title>GATA3</title>
      <link>/genepanel/2625/info/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 05 May 2019 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>/genepanel/2625/info/</guid>
      <description>


&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GATA binding protein 3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;left&#34; style=&#34;font-size:16px&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENTREZID: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/2625&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;2625&lt;/a&gt; | Type: Protein Coding |
Map: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genome/gdv/browser/gene/?id=2625&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt; 10p14&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
OMIM: &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/614286&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;614286&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/614172&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;614172&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/614038&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;614038&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/601626&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;601626&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/137295&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;137295&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;justify&#34; style=&#34;font-size:16px&#34;&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Summary Entrez&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;This gene encodes a protein which belongs to the GATA family of transcription factors. The protein contains two GATA-type zinc fingers and is an important regulator of T-cell development and plays an important role in endothelial cell biology. Defects in this gene are the cause of hypoparathyroidism with sensorineural deafness and renal dysplasia. [provided by RefSeq, Nov 2009] &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
</description>
